The paper discusses the use of a dynamic reputational model and a dual labor market to address disparities in the labor market, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques for modeling and decision-making. This makes cs.AI the most likely category. The paper also discusses statistical parity and fairness interventions, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also touches on social and economic implications of labor market disparities, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and sociology (cs.SOC).
